p :::s50:::He tells Alla the story of how Custance was found , and Alla begins to pity the girl .
:::s52:::Just as the knight who murdered Hermengyld is swearing that Custance is the true murderer , he is struck down and his eyes burst out of his face , proving his guilt to Alla and the crowd .
p :::s53:::The knight is executed , Alla and many others convert to Christianity , and Custance and Alla marry .
p :::s54:::While Alla is away in Scotland , Custance gives birth to a boy named Mauricius .
:::s55:::Alla 's mother , Donegild , intercepts a letter from Custance to Alla and substitutes a counterfeit one that claims that the child is disfigured and bewitched .
:::s57:::Donegild substitutes a letter saying that Custance and her son are banished and should be sent away on the same ship on which Custance arrived .
p :::s59:::After many adventures at sea , including an attempted rape , Custance ends up back in Rome , where she reunites with Alla , who has made a pilgrimage there to atone for killing his mother .
p :::s61:::Alla and Custance return to England , but Alla dies after a year , so Custance returns , once more , to Rome .
